description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to be part of an innovative, dynamic organisation that is committed to delivering the best care by the best people? If so, NELFT is the place for you………..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NELFT provides award winning community and mental healthcare for over 2 million people, across London, Essex and Kent. We work to ensure our patients and families, feel confident that their health needs are well met. With an excellent reputation for research and development, our skilled health professionals are at the cutting edge of evidence-based innovation, opening up the possibilities for better ways of working and delivery of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to delivering the best care for our patients. The successful candidate will share this commitment and demonstrate our Trust values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NELFT has CAMHS services across Essex, Kent and Medway known as EWMHS (Emotional Wellbeing and Mental Health Services) and offers a fantastic opportunity for a CAMHS Consultant post in Southend on Sea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to 2.5 SPAs we are offering for this post an additional SPA so a competitive 11 PA Consultant Contract for you to develop a special interest in an area of your preference, which could be either clinical, QI or academic. We also offer flexible and part-time working arrangements and a generous relocation package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based in the EWMHS Southend Hub, Skyline Plaza, 45 Victoria Avenue, Southend on sea, Essex SS2 6BB. The post has a caseload that falls within the recommendations set by the Royal College of Psychiatrists. Referrals are both self-referrals or referrals by professionals including GP’s, Schools, Social Services and onwards referral from the Child Development Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be supported by a 0.8 Specialty Doctor and a multidisciplinary team and a dedicated medical secretary following multidisciplinary team discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an Essex ISS (Intensive Support Service) team that manages young people in crisis who do not need admission but do require intensive weekly follow up and risk management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your team will also be supported by a EWMHS Essex Learning Disability Team with a dedicated LD CAMHS Consultant Psychiatrist for young people with severe and complex neurodevelopmental disorder and an EWMHS Essex Eating Disorder team, with dedicated ED CAMHS Psychiatrist, for your people with Eating Disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’ll support your professional and personal development, with protected time dedicated to your growth. With a high profile R&amp;D Department, a great QI programme, an excellent CPD and various training opportunities NELFT has lots to offer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll not only benefit from the seaside landmarks of Southend on Sea, renowned beauty and great heritage of Essex, but also from its affordable housing opportunities, incredible schools and great connections to Central London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in discussing the opportunities that are available, have professional registration and speak fluent English, please contact Dr Viviana Porcari, Consultant Psychiatrist, Associate Medical Director for Essex , NELFT via email on Viviana.porcari@nelft.nhs.uk or via her P.A. Denise McNamara on 01277 695595&lt;/p&gt;
